Five children died at Mwihoko in Ruiru Constituency, Kiambu County, after falling into a 20-foot septic tank filled with water.
Ruiru OCPD Phineas Lingera told the Nation that the children, aged between three and seven years, were playing near the tank covered by shrubs.
It was filled with rainwater, he said. ''They were playing near a construction site, where a developer is setting up a house. A pit latrine is also under construction in the area. The children accidentally fell into the tank while playing,‚Äù Mr Lingera said.



