He said the children were from different families.
The bodies were taken to the Kenyatta University Funeral Home.
The incident comes a few months after five people died in Juja, Kiambu, when the walls of a quarry where they were mining stones caved in.
The county government has been complaining about abandoned quarry sites especially in Juja, Ndarugu, Ruiru and Thika town, which are left uncovered and dangerous.



